      <item>
        <title>Use zurb foundation with frontity</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[luisherranz]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hey <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/wazidshh">@wazidshh</a>, welcome to the community <img src="https://community.frontity.org/images/emoji/apple/smiley.png?v=9" title=":smiley:" class="emoji" alt=":smiley:"></p>
<p>Yes, but when using React is always recommended to use the React version. In this case of foundation that’s <a href="https://github.com/digiaonline/react-foundation" rel="nofollow noopener">React-Foundation</a>.</p>
<p>This line is not going to work tho:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-javascript">// Add Foundation to index.js
import 'foundation-sites/dist/css/foundation.min.css';
</code></pre>
<p>because we do a lot of CSS optimization and don’t allow css files on Frontity.</p>
<p>But I’m going to investigate a solution. I’ll let you know.</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/use-zurb-foundation-with-frontity/305/2">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
